					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tl333s" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1304786); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1304786&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610163647" alt="TL333s" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1304786)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tl333s" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1304786); return false;" >TL333s</a></span> <span class="odate time_1528931410 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">13 Jun 2018 23:10</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3834882">
									

<p>Goddamn. :D I upvoted literally for the first two footnotes, but there's so much stuff going on here, I would have by the end anyway. (And tried to!)</p>
<p>I've never seen the SPC dealt with in Serpents Hand format before. That was surreal. Also a little confusing, but then I haven't been too enamored with Team Bird's work to date, this being a major exception. Point being, I wouldn't be surprised if I missed something.</p>
<p>I was also a little thrown by JV's working with the Foundation against Thoth. They proclaimed not to be a worshipper, but I wasn't expecting a full-on antagonist here.</p>
<p>I like this, though, I really do. It's got a nice blend of serious and off-kilter, which is why I love SH formats to begin with. :)</p>

							</div>

								
					
